1. DEFINITIONS

1.1 "Governance Artefacts" means all proposal texts, resolutions, annexes,
SOPs, templates, drafting materials, diagrams, and other governance
documentation authored for, adopted by, or published under the DAO's
governance processes, including any such materials published in a proposal
registry, SOP registry, or template registry (each as may exist from time
to time).

1.2 "Repository Materials" means all content in this repository that is, or is
clearly intended to be, Governance Artefacts or support material for
Governance Artefacts (including schemas, metadata conventions, and
non-production reference tooling used solely to format, validate, render, or
index Governance Artefacts).
For avoidance of doubt, "Repository Materials" exclude any Confidential
Materials (as defined below) and exclude any underlying documents, runbooks,
SOPs, counterparty particulars, or other materials that are not published in
full in this repository, even if referenced by hash, digest, content
identifier, link, filename, or description.

1.3 "DAO Marks" means trademarks, trade names, logos, domain names, and
branding identifiers of the DAO or the Protocol (as applicable).

1.4 "MetaDAO" means the separate DAO / ecosystem commonly known as "MetaDAO"
(or any successor governance that is substantially similar in purpose and
continuity).

1.5 "MetaDAO Marks" means the "MetaDAO" name and any MetaDAO trademarks,
trade names, logos, domain names, and branding identifiers, which are owned or
controlled by MetaDAO (not by the DAO).

1.6 "MetaDAO IP" means MetaDAO's intellectual property, including (without
limitation) any MetaDAO governance portal, programs, mechanisms (including any
futarchy or prediction mechanisms), smart contracts, documentation, and
branding, except to the limited extent a specific item is expressly included
in the Repository Materials and is owned by the DAO as a Governance Artefact.

1.7 "MetaDAO Cohort" means any past, current, or future cohort or DAO within
the MetaDAO ecosystem (or any successor umbrella program that is substantially
similar in purpose), including its governance participants acting for
governance, documentation, or template reuse purposes.

1.8 "You" means the individual or entity exercising permissions under this
License.

1.9 "Production Implementations" means any production-grade software, source
code, binaries, deployments, infrastructure, configuration, trading logic,
rebalancer agents, automation, or operational methods used to operate any
Implementation or any strategy, other than non-production reference tooling
included in the Repository Materials under Section 1.2.

1.10 "Confidential Materials" means any non-public or security-sensitive or
operationally sensitive information, including without limitation: private
keys and signing infrastructure; incident-response runbooks; internal SOPs;
counterparty particulars designated as confidential; security controls; trade
secrets; and any unredacted/original versions of materials for which only a
redacted copy, summary, or hash/content identifier is published.

1.11 "Confidential Instruments" means any document, dataset, counterparty
particulars, SOP, runbook, security material, or other information that is
not included in the repository and is referenced only by hash, content
identifier (CID), checksum, commitment, or a redacted/summary representation.

1.12 "Hash Reference" means any hash, digest, CID, or other integrity anchor
included in the Repository Materials that identifies or commits to content
that may be withheld or separately stored.

