apply to embedded third-party components.

2.2 This License grants only the permissions expressly stated below. No other
rights are granted by implication, estoppel, or otherwise.

2.3 MetaDAO carve-out (no claim; no license). The DAO does not claim ownership
of, and this License does not grant any rights in, MetaDAO Marks or MetaDAO
IP. Any reference in the Repository Materials to MetaDAO governance, programs,
mechanisms, or portals is purely referential unless an item is expressly
identified as a Governance Artefact owned by the DAO.

2.4 Access to MetaDAO systems. Any access to, or use of, MetaDAO portals,
systems, or programs is governed solely by MetaDAO's own terms and
permissions.
Nothing in this License grants access rights to MetaDAO infrastructure.

2.5 Hash references are integrity anchors only. A Hash Reference is published
solely to enable integrity verification and does not constitute publication
of, or grant any license to, the underlying Confidential Instrument.

2.6 Relationship to Company Agreement and IP License Framework. This License
governs public governance repositories only. It is a repository-content license
for Repository Materials and does not amend, override, expand, or interpret the
Company Agreement instrument hierarchy.

Licensing of Protocol IP for deployment or commercial use is governed
exclusively by the IP License Framework (a Primary Instrument of the Company
Agreement) and requires a License granted under it. Nothing in this License or
the Repository Materials constitutes or implies a grant under the IP License
Framework.

For avoidance of doubt, publication of SOPs, templates, standards, examples,
checklists, or other Repository Materials does not constitute direction,
control, supervision, approval, or orchestration of any Licensee's business,
operations, compliance posture, or Licensee Declaration. Any Licensee's use or
non-use of Repository Materials is the independent decision of that Licensee,
and no agency, partnership, joint venture, common enterprise, or representative
relationship is created by such publication or use.

2.7 Authoritative record; no governance effect by repository presence. This
License governs repository use only. It does not, by itself, adopt, amend,
ratify, approve, or make effective any governance instrument, Resolution,
Operational Pack, or other Company Agreement instrument.
Whether any Repository Material is adopted, current, or binding is determined
solely by the DAO's governance system / on-chain record, formally executed or
filed instruments (as applicable), and the authoritative records maintained
under the Company Agreement.
If a repository copy differs from an adopted/authoritative record, the
adopted/authoritative record controls.
Nothing in this License expands authority beyond the Company Agreement,
the order of precedence established in it, or on-chain constraints.

