7.2 You grant the DAO a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free
license to use, reproduce, modify, sublicense, and distribute Your
Contribution as part of the Repository Materials and as Governance Artefacts,
under any terms the DAO may adopt for governance repositories (including this
License and any successor license adopted by governance).

7.3 No Governance Status from Contribution Workflow. A Contribution, and any
review, moderation, acceptance, merge, or publication of that Contribution,
does not by itself make it an adopted, ratified, current, or effective DAO
instrument. Governance effect (if any) arises only through the DAO's
governance mechanisms and authoritative records under the Company Agreement.

7.4 No Relationship Created by Contribution Workflow. Submitting, reviewing,
moderating, maintaining, or merging repository content does not create any
agency, partnership, joint venture, employment, fiduciary, counsel, or other
representative relationship with the DAO.
It does not confer Membership, Subcommittee status, voting rights, economic
rights, or authority under the Company Agreement.
No person may bind, represent, or speak on behalf of the DAO by reason only
of repository activity, role labels, or repository permissions.

7.5 No Contribution, pull request, issue, discussion, review,
moderation activity, or repository maintenance activity creates Membership,
Subcommittee status, employment, agency, fiduciary duty, or representative
authority with respect to the DAO.

